in Fig. 4, the left subÔ¨Ågure is all identiÔ¨Åed positions in Oslo port using PD-DBSCAN. The right three subÔ¨Ågures represent zoom-in areas in the left subÔ¨Ågure. Quays are partitioned based on berths‚Äô position and functionality as labelled by the number from 1 to 7. Fig. 5 shows the Ô¨Çow of different ship types to all quays. Therein, quay 2 is a ferry and cruise area; quay 5 is a container area; tankers stop in quay 6; other quays have different ship types.
After berth identiÔ¨Åcation, arrival time and departure time could be identiÔ¨Åed. Next, all information is merged together, including MMSI, ship types, ship deadweight, berthing time, arrival time, quay, etc. In this study, features like frequency, deadweight, and berthing time will be used for knowledge discovery.

B. Year-on-Year Impact Analysis
This part aims to verify the superiority of DTW to analyse abnormal patterns against other well-known classic similarity measuring methods. Besides DTW, longest common subsequence (LCSS), edit distance with real penalty (ERP), and edit distance on real sequences (EDR) could provide a better match with another time series. They are able to compare different time sequences that are of different lengths and out of phase in time [32]. However, EDR and EPR are not suitable for large time-shifting sequences. Hence, in this study, DTW and LCSS are selected to Ô¨Ånd the period of abnormal patterns and evaluate the similarity of different time-

Fig. 8. DTW analysis of ferry‚Äôs Ô¨Çow before COVID-19.
series sequences. The similarity measuring function of DTW is selected as Manhattan. Then, it is used to analyse the variation of ship Ô¨Çow, daily throughout, and berthing time of quays yearon-year. On the one hand, the discovered knowledge could support stakeholders‚Äô decisions in the next crisis. On the other hand, it could be used to Ô¨Ånd out an impact threshold for the short-term impact analysis with the help of signiÔ¨Åcance interval estimation.
Table I lists the total frequency of different ships during four years. From this table, it can be seen that business Ô¨Çeets

