signiÔ¨Åcance interval estimation is selected to Ô¨Ånd a threshold for the short-term analysis of COVID-19 inÔ¨Çuences.
The proposed method can be used to carry out COVID-19 impacts analysis in two respects: year-on-year and month-onmonth. Through year-on-year comparisons, different patterns are discovered in terms of ship Ô¨Çow and quays‚Äô operations. For example, the passenger ships are inÔ¨Çuenced by COVID-19 heavily while cargo ships are not. The mined knowledge could be used for economic policy-making and port management if extreme quarantine measures are required in the next health crisis. Month-on-month impact analysis is mainly to observe the short-term variation trend combined with different risk levels. Based on the historical trend, it is beneÔ¨Åcial to provide supports for short-term decision-making.
Due to limited data points, machine learning and regression analysis do not work well in constructing an accurate impact prediction model. In future work, sufÔ¨Åcient data to support accurate model construction should be collected.
